<stack-static>
    <statement><p><p>
A rectangular garden has the following dimensions:
</p>
<ul>
<li>Length = <m> (x + {2}) </m> metres</li>
<li>Width = <m> (x + {6}) </m> metres</li>
</ul>
<p>
(a) Write an expression for the area of the garden.
</p>
<p>
(b) Expand and simplify your answer.
</p>
<p>
<fillin characters="15" name="ans1"/>  
</p></p></statement>
    <solution><p><h3>Worked Solution</h3>

<p>
Area of a rectangle = length × width.
</p>

<p>
<me>
(x + {2})(x + {6})
</me>
</p>

<p>
Step 1: Multiply <m>x</m> by both terms in the second bracket.
</p>

<p>
<me>
x(x + {6}) = x^2 + {6}x
</me>
</p>

<p>
Step 2: Multiply <m>{2}</m> by both terms in the second bracket.
</p>

<p>
<me>
{2}(x + {6}) = {2}x + {12}
</me>
</p>

<p>
Step 3: Add the results.
</p>

<p>
<me>
x^2 + {6}x + {2}x + {12}
</me>
</p>

<p>
Step 4: Combine like terms.
</p>

<p>
<me>
= x^2 + {8}x + {12}
</me>
</p>

<p>
Therefore, the area in simplest form is:
</p>

<p>
<me>
x^2 + {8}x + {12}
</me>
</p></p></solution>
    <answer><p><m>x^2+8 x+12</m></p></answer>
</stack-static>